   139	### 1. Template Discovery, Listing, Layout, And Manifest Validation
   140	
   141	Normative claims:
   142	
   143	- A template is a directory with required `template.yaml`, optional
   144	  `states.yaml`, exactly one plan entry point (`plan.rhei.md` or
   145	  `index.rhei.md` + `tasks/`), optional `settings.json`, and additional files.
   146	- Template names are directory names and identifiers for CLI commands.
   147	- Named template discovery is first-match-wins: project
   148	  `<project>/.agents/rhei/templates/<name>/`, then user
   149	  `~/.agents/rhei/templates/<name>/`.
   150	- `rhei templates` lists discovered templates, supports `--json` and
   151	  `--source <project|user|all>`, prints name/version/description/source/path
   152	  and required input count, and skips invalid/unreadable template directories
   153	  with a warning.
   154	- `rhei instantiate <name>` fails if the matched template is invalid; direct
   155	  path references bypass named discovery and fail if unreadable or invalid.
   156	- `template.yaml` schema fields are `name`, `version`, `description`, and
   157	  optional `inputs`; key order is not normative.
   158	- Manifest `name` must match the enclosing directory; `description` must be
   159	  non-empty; input names are unique identifiers; `version` is a displayed YAML
   160	  scalar with no semantic-version validation.
   161	- Input types are `string`, `number`, `boolean`, `path`, `array`, `object`,
   162	  defaulting to `string`.
   163	- `required: true` is mutually exclusive with `default`; a `default` makes the
   164	  input optional; optional no-default inputs resolve to type-shaped empties.
   165	- `positional` is a positive integer; positional indexes are unique and
   166	  contiguous from `1`.
   167	- `type: array` requires `items`; `type: object` may declare `properties`,
   168	  whose members are required unless `required: false` or `default` is present.
   169	- `validate` is only valid on scalar input types and is a Rust `regex` pattern
   170	  anchored to the whole rendered scalar value.
