   215	### 2. Template Instantiation, Rendering, Settings, Validation, Summary, And Execution
   216	
   217	Normative claims:
   218	
   219	- `rhei instantiate` accepts a template name or filesystem path, positional
   220	  inputs, bare `KEY=VALUE`, `--set`, `--set-file`, repeatable `--values`,
   221	  `--output`, `--execute`, `--dry-run`, `--keep-on-error`, and `--list-inputs`.
   222	- Input precedence is: manifest defaults, then `--values` files left-to-right,
   223	  then positional inputs, then bare `KEY=VALUE` and `--set` left-to-right, then
   224	  `--set-file` left-to-right.
   225	- A template can declare explicit positional inputs. If it declares exactly one
   226	  required input and no positional fields, one bare value maps to that input.
   227	- `KEY=VALUE` is an assignment only when `KEY` is a valid declared input name;
   228	  values containing `=` with a non-input prefix remain positional.
   229	- Duplicate input sources are allowed and later values in a precedence group
   230	  override earlier values.
   231	- Array/object values from positional input, bare assignments, `--set`, and
   232	  `--set-file` are parsed as YAML/JSON snippets before validation.
   233	- `type: path` values are rendered exactly as supplied or defaulted. The CLI
   234	  should not rewrite them to absolute paths except when resolving a path for
   235	  CLI file operations; omitted optional paths resolve to `""`.
   236	- Rendering uses strict MiniJinja syntax: `{{ expr }}`, `{% for %}`,
   237	  `{% if %}`, `{% raw %}`, and `|slug`; missing variables or properties fail.
   238	- Runtime single-brace variables such as `{task_id}` and
   239	  `{output.name.path}` pass through instantiation untouched.
   240	- `template.yaml` is parsed before rendering, is never templated, and is
   241	  excluded from output.
   242	- Text files are rendered if no null byte appears in the first 8 KiB; binary
   243	  files are copied verbatim; text files must decode as UTF-8.
   244	- `\{{` remains a legacy literal `{{` escape.
   245	- Hidden files/directories and `template.yaml` are excluded from output.
   246	- A root-level template `settings.json` is rendered and moved to
   247	  `.rhei/settings.json` in the output; it must parse as UTF-8 JSON after
   248	  rendering; `${VAR}` secret expansion belongs to runtime settings, not
   249	  instantiation.
   250	- `--output` defaults to `./<template-name>/` and must not already exist in
   251	  normal mode; normal instantiation fails instead of merging or overwriting.
   252	- `--dry-run` materializes into scratch space, skips the requested output path
   253	  existence check, validates the scratch output, reports the requested output
   254	  tree, and writes nothing at the requested output path.
   255	- File permissions and directory structure are preserved for materialized
   256	  files except the root `settings.json` relocation.
   257	- Instantiation runs `rhei validate` after rendering. If the output root has
   258	  `states.yaml`, that file is the state machine; otherwise validation uses the
   259	  built-in default. Settings are composed from global settings and output-root
   260	  `.rhei/settings.json`.
   261	- Validation warnings are printed; validation errors abort and remove output
   262	  unless `--keep-on-error` is passed.
   263	- Successful instantiation prints the specified summary headings and content:
   264	  output path, task/state counts, files, task tree, recent task definitions,
   265	  stop reason, and a reproducible shell-safe `rhei instantiate ... --output`
   266	  invocation.
   267	- Stop reasons distinguish dry-run, already-complete plans, human gates, next
   268	  ready task, blocked tasks, and no claimable task.
   269	- `--execute` runs `rhei run <output>` after successful validation and uses
   270	  the instantiated root `states.yaml` by default when present.
   271	- Exit code `0` means success; exit code `1` covers lookup, input, render,
   272	  output conflict, validation, or execution errors.
   273	- The parser never sees `{{...}}`; templates are a preprocessing layer that
   274	  must produce valid Rhei documents.
