   645	### 6. Shell Completion Generation, Installation, Dynamic Context, And Candidate Coverage
   646	
   647	Normative claims:
   648	
   649	- `rhei completions <SHELL>` writes only the completion script to stdout
   650	  unless installation/output options are supplied.
   651	- Supported shells are `bash`, `zsh`, `fish`, `powershell`, and `elvish`.
   652	- `--install` writes to the shell's default user or system path; `--system`
   653	  chooses system paths; `--output <PATH>` writes to an explicit path;
   654	  `--dry-run` prints the destination path without writing.
   655	- Install creates parent directories and overwrites the completion file
   656	  atomically enough for normal CLI use.
   657	- Generated scripts call back into the current `rhei` binary through the
   658	  `COMPLETE` environment variable and should reflect command tree, global
   659	  flags, value enums, dynamic values, and template input arguments.
   660	- Completions are advisory and must not mutate plans or metadata, acquire task
   661	  locks, run callbacks, spawn agents/programs, use the network, or print
   662	  human diagnostics to stdout during dynamic completion.
   663	- Completion must degrade quietly when plans, workspaces, state machines,
   664	  settings files, values files, or template manifests cannot be read.
   665	- Completion should filter by current prefix, preserve shell quoting/escaping,
   666	  and provide help text where supported.
   667	- Filesystem completion domains:
   668	  - `RHEI_PLAN`: `.rhei.md` files and workspace directories containing
   669	    `index.rhei.md`, with directories traversable.
   670	  - `--state-machine`: `.yaml` and `.yml`.
   671	  - `--values`: `.yaml`, `.yml`, `.json`.
   672	  - `--output`: directories and new leaf paths.
   673	  - `completions --output`: files and new leaf paths.
   674	  - `--set-file KEY=PATH`: file paths after `=`.
   675	  - template `type: path`: files and directories.
   676	- Command coverage includes global `--state-machine`, plan positionals,
   677	  render format values, list filters, template sources, instantiate template
   678	  names and inputs, run agent/mode/model/timeout/parallel values, next/complete
   679	  task ids, transition task/from/to state values, reset plan paths,
   680	  install-skills agent and comma-aware skill values, and completions shell
   681	  names.
   682	- `rhei instantiate <TEMPLATE>` completes project templates before user
   683	  templates, hides user duplicates when project duplicates exist, shows
   684	  template description/source, and switches to directory completion for
   685	  path-like template references.
   686	- Template input completion parses the command line using instantiation
   687	  precedence, offers the next positional slot or single-required-input
   688	  fallback, suggests remaining `KEY=` assignments, hides supplied
   689	  non-repeatable input keys unless editing that key, and completes right-hand
   690	  values by type.
   691	- `--set-file` completes keys like `--set` but always uses file completion for
   692	  the value.
   693	- `--values` completion may parse readable YAML/JSON values files for ranking
   694	  but must ignore parse failures.
   695	- `--list-inputs` should not require required inputs.
   696	- Task/state completion reads plan/workspace data and resolved state machine
   697	  without claiming tasks or triggering side effects.
   698	- `rhei list --state` is comma-aware; `--assignee`, `--kind`, `--has-prior`,
   699	  and `--parent` complete values present in the selected plan/workspace.
   700	- `rhei transition --from` uses the selected task's current state when known;
   701	  `--to` uses allowed target states from the known/selected from state.
   702	- `rhei run --agent`, `--agent-mode`, and `--model` complete from the same
   703	  merged settings and state-machine resolution used by execution.
   704	- `rhei install-skills --skills` is comma-aware and avoids duplicating already
   705	  supplied skills.
   706	- Acceptance tests should cover every command and dynamic area listed in the
   707	  completions spec.
