   198	
   199	## Template Input Completion
   200	
   201	`rhei instantiate` has the richest completion behavior because the valid
   202	arguments depend on the selected template. Completion must parse the command
   203	line to identify:
   204	
   205	1. The selected template name or path.
   206	2. The template manifest inputs.
   207	3. Inputs already supplied by positional values, bare `KEY=VALUE`, `--set`,
   208	   `--set-file`, and `--values`.
   209	4. The cursor token currently being edited.
   210	
   211	The parser used for completion should follow the same rules as instantiation:
   212	manifest defaults < `--values` files < positional input values < bare
   213	`KEY=VALUE` and `--set` < `--set-file`.
   214	
   215	### Template Name Slot
   216	
   217	Before a template is selected:
   218	
   219	- Complete project templates first, then user templates.
   220	- Show the template description as candidate help.
   221	- If a project and user template share a name, show only the project template.
   222	- If the current token is path-like, complete directories instead of template
   223	  names.
   224	
   225	### Positional Slots
   226	
   227	After a template is selected, a bare argument without `=` completes the next
   228	available positional input.
   229	
   230	Given:
   231	
   232	```yaml
   233	inputs:
   234	  - name: spec
   235	    type: path
   236	    positional: 1
   237	  - name: criteria
   238	    type: string
   239	    required: false
   240	```
   241	
   242	the cursor in this command completes filesystem paths for `spec`:
   243	
   244	```bash
   245	rhei instantiate spec-review <TAB>
   246	```
   247	
   248	After the first positional value is present, completion should stop suggesting a
   249	second bare positional unless the manifest declares `positional: 2`:
   250	
   251	```bash
   252	rhei instantiate spec-review docs/rhei.spec.md <TAB>
   253	```
   254	
   255	At that point candidates should be remaining input assignments such as
   256	`criteria=`, plus normal flags.
   257	
   258	If a template declares exactly one required input and no `positional` fields,
   259	completion treats the first bare value as that input. This matches the
   260	single-required-input fallback in the template spec.
   261	
   262	If completion cannot determine a valid positional slot, it should suggest
   263	remaining `KEY=` assignments rather than inventing a positional meaning.
   264	
   265	### Assignment Keys
   266	
   267	At any input position after the template name, completion should suggest
   268	remaining input assignment keys as `KEY=`:
   269	
   270	```bash
   271	rhei instantiate code-review <TAB>
   272	# target=       review_passes=       model=
   273	```
   274	
   275	Assignments are available both as bare input arguments and as `--set` values:
   276	
   277	```bash
   278	rhei instantiate code-review target=src <TAB>
   279	rhei instantiate code-review --set <TAB>
   280	```
   281	
   282	Candidate help should include:
   283	
   284	```text
   285	path, required, positional 1 - File or directory to review
   286	number, default 2 - Number of review iterations
   287	string, default claude - Model to use for review
   288	```
   289	
   290	Inputs already supplied by an explicit assignment should be hidden from the
   291	normal suggestion list. They may reappear when the current token is editing the
   292	same input because overriding an input remains legal.
   293	
   294	### Assignment Values
   295	
   296	When the cursor is after `KEY=`, complete the value according to the input type:
   297	
   298	| Input type | Value completion |
   299	|------------|------------------|
   300	| `path` | File and directory paths |
   301	| `boolean` | `true`, `false` |
   302	| `number` | No fixed values unless the input declares examples in a future manifest extension |
   303	| `string` | No fixed values unless the input declares examples in a future manifest extension |
   304	| `array` | Snippets `[]`, `[item]` where supported; otherwise no fixed values |
   305	| `object` | Snippets `{}` where supported; otherwise no fixed values |
   306	
   307	Examples:
   308	
   309	```bash
   310	rhei instantiate spec-review spec=<TAB>          # path completion
   311	rhei instantiate foo enabled=<TAB>               # true / false
   312	rhei instantiate foo --set target=<TAB>          # path completion when target is type:path
   313	rhei instantiate foo --set-file prompt=<TAB>     # file path completion
   314	```
   315	
   316	For `--set-file KEY=PATH`, the key completes like `--set`, but the value always
   317	uses file path completion regardless of the input type because the value is read
   318	from disk.
   319	
   320	### Values Files
   321	
   322	When one or more `--values` files are present, completion may parse readable
   323	YAML/JSON files to suppress already-supplied input keys. Failure to parse a
   324	values file must not fail completion; it only means those values are ignored for
   325	completion ranking.
   326	
   327	`--values <TAB>` completes `.yaml`, `.yml`, and `.json` files.
   328	
   329	### List Inputs Mode
   330	
   331	`--list-inputs` does not require user-supplied required inputs. Completion after
   332	`--list-inputs` should still offer flags such as `--values` and `--output` only
   333	when they remain syntactically valid, but it should not pressure the user to
   334	fill required template inputs.
   335	
   336	### Unknown Or Invalid Templates
   337	
   338	If the template cannot be found or its manifest cannot be parsed, completion
   339	should still offer:
   340	
   341	- Static flags and options for `rhei instantiate`.
   342	- Path completion for path-like template references.
   343	- No template-specific input candidates.
   344	
   345	The shell must not display parse errors as completion candidates.
   346	
   347	## Task And State Completion
   348	
   349	Commands that inspect or operate on tasks should complete task and plan-derived
   350	values after a plan/workspace argument is present:
   351	
   352	```bash
   353	rhei list plan.rhei.md --has-prior <TAB>
   354	rhei list plan.rhei.md --state dra<TAB>
   355	rhei next plan.rhei.md --task <TAB>
   356	rhei complete workspace/ --task <TAB>
   357	rhei transition workspace/ --task <TAB>
   358	```
   359	
   360	Task candidates use the task id as the inserted value. Help should include the
   361	task title and current state:
   362	
   363	```text
   364	1       Write initial draft [draft]
   365	auth    Review auth module [review]
   366	```
   367	
   368	`rhei transition --from` and `--to` should use the resolved state machine:
   369	
   370	- `--from` completes the selected task's current state when `--task` is known.
   371	- Without a known task, `--from` completes all state names.
   372	- `--to` completes allowed target states from the selected `--from`.
   373	- If `--from` is omitted but `--task` is known, `--to` completes allowed target
   374	  states from the task's current state.
   375	- State candidate help should include state descriptions when available.
   376	
   377	Completion must not claim a task, alter `**Assignee:**`, run callbacks, or
   378	evaluate transition conditions with side effects.
   379	
   380	`rhei list` filter completion should use values that actually occur in the
   381	selected plan/workspace when possible:
   382	
   383	- `--state` completes state names and aliases from the resolved state machine.
   384	  The option is comma-aware and replaces only the segment after the last comma.
   385	- `--assignee` completes distinct `**Assignee:**` values present in the plan.
   386	- `--kind` completes distinct task/node kinds present in the plan.
   387	- `--has-prior` and `--parent` complete task ids.
   388	- `--contains` remains free text.
   389	- `--limit` completes useful numeric examples but accepts any non-negative
   390	  integer.
   391	
   392	## Agent And Skill Completion
   393	
   394	`rhei run` should complete agent-related overrides from the same merged settings
   395	and state-machine resolution used by execution:
   396	
   397	- `--agent` completes configured agent names.
   398	- `--agent-mode` completes modes for the selected agent when `--agent` is
   399	  present; otherwise it completes the union of known modes.
   400	- `--model` completes configured model aliases and model ids when available.
   401	
   402	`rhei install-skills --skills` is comma-aware:
   403	
   404	```bash
   405	rhei install-skills --skills rhei-plan-<TAB>
   406	rhei install-skills --skills rhei-plan-worker,rhei-<TAB>
   407	```
   408	
   409	Completion should replace only the segment after the last comma and should not
   410	duplicate skills already present in the comma-separated list.
   411	
   412	## Performance And Reliability
   413	
   414	Completion should feel instant. Implementations should prefer shallow,
   415	targeted reads over full validation:
   416	
   417	- Template name completion reads only template manifests.
   418	- Template input completion reads only the selected manifest and optionally
   419	  supplied values files.
   420	- Task completion parses the selected plan/workspace but does not run full
   421	  validation unless validation data is already needed for state completion.
   422	- State completion loads the selected or auto-discovered state machine.
   423	
   424	Completion should avoid unbounded directory walks. Project/user template roots
   425	and workspace task directories may be scanned; arbitrary recursive scans should
   426	be avoided unless the shell's path completer owns the traversal.
   427	
   428	## Acceptance Tests
   429	
   430	The completion test suite should cover at least:
   431	
   432	- Every subcommand appears at `rhei <TAB>`.
   433	- Every value enum completes from the parser's enum source.
   434	- `RHEI_PLAN`, `--state-machine`, `--values`, `--output`, and `--set-file`
   435	  path completion use the expected path domain.
   436	- `instantiate` completes project/user template names with project precedence.
   437	- `instantiate` completes positional `type: path` inputs as paths.
   438	- `instantiate` completes remaining input keys as `KEY=`.
   439	- `instantiate` completes `KEY=` right-hand sides by input type.
   440	- `instantiate --set` and bare `KEY=VALUE` share key/value completion behavior.
   441	- `instantiate --set-file` completes keys and then file paths.
   442	- Single-required-input fallback completes the first bare value using that
   443	  input's type.
   444	- Already supplied input keys are not suggested again unless editing that token.
   445	- `next`, `complete`, and `transition` complete task ids from a plan/workspace.
   446	- `transition --from` and `--to` complete state names from the resolved state
   447	  machine.
   448	- `install-skills --skills` completes comma-separated skill segments.
   449	- Invalid manifests, unreadable plans, and unreadable values files degrade
   450	  without stdout diagnostics.
   451	
   452	## System Installation
   453	
   454	`cargo install` only installs the `rhei` binary. It cannot install shell completion files by itself.
   455	
   456	System packages, distro packages, Homebrew formulae, and local install scripts should install the binary first, then run one completion install command per supported shell:
   457	
   458	```bash
   459	rhei completions bash --install --system
   460	rhei completions zsh --install --system
   461	rhei completions fish --install --system
   462	rhei completions powershell --install --system
   463	rhei completions elvish --install --system
   464	```
   465	
   466	PowerShell and Elvish system paths are provided for package scripts that manage those runtimes, but users may still need to source the generated file from their profile depending on their local shell configuration.
   467	
   468	## Examples
   469	
   470	Install Fish completions:
   471	
   472	```bash
   473	mkdir -p ~/.config/fish/completions
   474	rhei completions fish > ~/.config/fish/completions/rhei.fish
   475	```
   476	
   477	Install Fish completions to the default user path:
   478	
   479	```bash
   480	rhei completions fish --install
   481	```
   482	
   483	Generate Zsh completions into a local completion directory:
   484	
   485	```bash
   486	mkdir -p ~/.zfunc
   487	rhei completions zsh > ~/.zfunc/_rhei
   488	```
   489	
   490	Preview Bash completions without installing them:
   491	
   492	```bash
   493	rhei completions bash
   494	```
   495	
   496	## Non-Goals
   497	
   498	- `rhei completions` does not edit shell rc files, profiles, or startup scripts.
   499	- It does not generate completions for external agent commands spawned by `rhei run`.
   500	
   501	## Related Specifications
   502	
   503	- [Templates Specification](rhei-templates.spec.md) — Template input syntax,
   504	  positional inputs, and instantiation precedence.
   505	- [List Command](rhei-list.spec.md) — Task listing filters that provide dynamic
   506	  completion sources.
   507	- [States Specification](rhei-states.spec.md) — State names, aliases, terminal
   508	  states, and transition metadata.
   509	- [Agents Specification](rhei-agents.spec.md) — Agent, mode, model, and settings
   510	  resolution.

