     1	# `rhei install-skills`
     2	
     3	Install rhei skills (plan-writer, plan-worker, state-machine-writer) into the configuration directories of major AI coding agents, so any agent session can invoke them without per-project setup. Supports both global (user-level) and project-local installation.
     4	
     5	## Usage
     6	
     7	```
     8	rhei install-skills [OPTIONS]
     9	rhei install-skills --agent claude-code
    10	rhei install-skills --agent cursor
    11	rhei install-skills --agent all
    12	rhei install-skills --local --agent claude-code
    13	rhei install-skills --uninstall --agent claude-code
    14	```
    15	
    16	## Options
    17	
    18	| Flag | Default | Description |
    19	|------|---------|-------------|
    20	| `--agent <NAME>` | `all` | Target agent: `claude-code`, `cursor`, `windsurf`, `copilot`, `kilocode`, `pi`, `codex`, `antigravity`, or `all` |
    21	| `--local` | | Install into the current project directory instead of global user config |
    22	| `--link` | | Symlink skill files instead of copying (stays up-to-date with rhei releases) |
    23	| `--uninstall` | | Remove previously installed skills |
    24	| `--dry-run` | | Print what would be done without changing anything |
    25	| `--skills <LIST>` | `rhei-plan-writer,rhei-plan-worker,rhei-state-machine-writer` | Comma-separated list of skills to install |
    26	
    27	## Agent Targets
    28	
    29	Each agent has a different configuration layout. The command handles each one. The tables below show global (default) and project-local (`--local`) paths.
    30	
    31	### Claude Code (`claude-code`)
    32	
    33	| Mode | Skill files | Registration |
    34	|------|-------------|--------------|
    35	| Global | `~/.claude/skills/rhei-<skill>/` | `~/.claude/CLAUDE.md` |
    36	| Local | `.claude/skills/rhei-<skill>/` | `.claude/CLAUDE.md` (project root) |
    37	
    38	**Registration:** Append a section to the target `CLAUDE.md`:
    39	
    40	```markdown
    41	# rhei
    42	- **rhei-plan-writer** (`~/.claude/skills/rhei-plan-writer/SKILL.md`) — create and validate Rhei Plans. Trigger: `/rhei-plan-writer`
    43	- **rhei-plan-worker** (`~/.claude/skills/rhei-plan-worker/SKILL.md`) — execute tasks in a Rhei Plan. Trigger: `/rhei-plan-worker <plan>`
    44	- **rhei-state-machine-writer** (`~/.claude/skills/rhei-state-machine-writer/SKILL.md`) — design custom state machines from project specs and teams. Trigger: `/rhei-state-machine-writer`
    45	When the user types `/rhei-plan-writer`, `/rhei-plan-worker`, or `/rhei-state-machine-writer`, invoke the Skill tool with the corresponding skill name before doing anything else.
    46	```
    47	
    48	In local mode, the paths in the registration block use relative paths (e.g., `.claude/skills/rhei-plan-writer/SKILL.md`).
    49	
    50	### Cursor (`cursor`)
    51	
    52	| Mode | Skill files |
    53	|------|-------------|
    54	| Global | `~/.cursor/rules/rhei-<skill>.mdc` |
    55	| Local | `.cursor/rules/rhei-<skill>.mdc` (project root) |
