     9	## SMT-001: YAML State Machine Root Schema and Default Machine
    10	
    11	- **implementation-diverges**: The specification says the machine-readable default is `docs/specs/states.yaml`, version `3.0`, with `profiles` and `node_policy`. The compiled default used by `StateMachine::builtin_default()` is `crates/rhei-validator/src/default-states.yaml`, version `2.0`, with `draft.initial: true` and no profiles/node policy. Evidence: `docs/specs/states.yaml:5`, `docs/specs/states.yaml:107`, `docs/specs/states.yaml:125`; `crates/rhei-validator/src/default-states.yaml:5`, `crates/rhei-validator/src/default-states.yaml:16`; `crates/rhei-validator/src/lib.rs:641`.
    12	- **implementation-diverges**: State machines without `profiles` and `node_policy` still load as legacy machines, even though the current specs mark both as required and state-level `initial: true` forbidden. Evidence: `docs/specs/rhei-states.spec.md:91`; `docs/specs/rhei-states.spec.md:101`; `crates/rhei-validator/src/lib.rs:631`; `crates/rhei-validator/src/lib.rs:1021`.
    13	- **missing-validation**: `transitions` is declared required by the transition spec, but `StateMachine` defaults it to an empty list when omitted. Evidence: `docs/specs/rhei-transitions.spec.md:536`; `crates/rhei-validator/src/lib.rs:626`.
    14	- **no-discrepancy**: `rhei complete` selects a one-hop non-cancelled terminal transition and refuses to fall back to `cancelled`. Evidence: `crates/rhei-cli/src/main.rs:9615`; tests at `crates/rhei-cli/src/main.rs:11597`, `crates/rhei-cli/src/main.rs:11617`, and `crates/rhei-cli/src/main.rs:11634`.
    15	
    16	## SMT-002: Profiles and Node Policy
    17	
    18	- **implementation-diverges**: The spec defines `overrides[].match` as an object with optional `type` and `level`, but the implementation models it as a string `pattern` matched exactly against task id. Evidence: `docs/specs/rhei-states.spec.md:778`; `docs/specs/rhei-states.spec.md:791`; `crates/rhei-validator/src/lib.rs:601`; `crates/rhei-validator/src/lib.rs:672`.
