   189	
   190	### SY-003-B: Duplicate `**State:**` lines are accepted by overwriting
   191	
   192	Classification: `missing-validation`
   193	
   194	The grammar has exactly one `state_field`. The parser has a duplicate guard for `**Assignee:**`, but `**State:**` parsing simply assigns `top.state = Some(...)` each time it sees a state line before content, so a second state line silently replaces the first. Evidence:
