   202	
   203	### SY-003-C: `**Prior:**` list shape is only partially parsed
   204	
   205	Classification: `missing-validation`
   206	
   207	The grammar requires `**Prior:**` to be a comma-space separated list of kind-qualified task references. The parser accepts any line starting with `**Prior:**`, extracts every regex match it can find, and extends the prior list with those ids. It does not require the whole line to match the grammar, does not reject an empty prior list, and does not validate separators. Evidence:
